.\" cligPart NAME
.SH NAME
downsample \- Downsamples a time series.
.\" cligPart NAME end

.\" cligPart SYNOPSIS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B downsample
-factor factor
[-o outfile]
[--] file
.\" cligPart SYNOPSIS end

.\" cligPart OPTIONS
.SH OPTIONS
.IP -factor
The factor to downsample the data,
.br
1 Int value between 1 and 100.
.IP -o
Name of the output time series file (with suffix),
.br
1 String value
.IP file
Input '.dat' or '.sdat' file name.
.\" cligPart OPTIONS end

.\" cligPart DESCRIPTION
.SH DESCRIPTION
downsample co-adds every
.B -factor
neighboring samples of an already-dedispersed PRESTO time series
.RI ( .dat
or
.IR .sdat ,
as produced by
.BR prepdata (1)
or
.BR prepsubband (1)),
writing a new, shorter time series
.RI ( <root>_D<factor>.dat / .sdat
by default, or
.B -o
if given).  This is occasionally useful after the fact -- e.g. to
further reduce the time resolution of an existing
.I .dat
file for a long-period search -- without having to re-run
dedispersion from the raw data with a different
.B -downsamp
value.

.\" cligPart DESCRIPTION end

